  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Add your <strong>butternut squash cubes </strong>to a baking tray (or two!) with a drizzle of<strong> vegetable oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up and put the tray[s] in the oven for 15-20 min or until tender and golden</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1633344089914-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1633344089914-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1633344089914-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1633344089914-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1633344089914-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Rinse your <strong>brown rice</strong>, then add it to a pot with plenty of <strong>cold water</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium and cook for 20-25 min or until it's tender with a slight bite</p><p>Once cooked, drain and return it to the pot and keep covered until serving</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1633344093224-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1633344093224-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1633344093224-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1633344093224-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1633344093224-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the rice is cooking, heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add your <strong>coriander seeds</strong> and cook for 1 min or until fragrant</p><p>Once fragrant, transfer the <strong>coriander seeds</strong> to a <strong>pestle & mortar</strong> and crush roughly</p><p>Reserve the pan</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1633344094644-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1633344094644-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1633344094644-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1633344094644-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1633344094644-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, boil half a kettle</p><p>Peel and finely slice your <strong>brown onion[s]</strong></p><p>Return the pan to a medium-low heat with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil </strong>and the <strong>sliced onion</strong></p><p>Cook for 4-5 min or until softened</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1633344095790-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1633344095790-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1633344095790-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1633344095790-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1633344095790-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Peel (scrape the skin off with a teaspoon) and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>ginger</strong></p><p>Chop your<strong> creamed coconut</strong> roughly (if required!)</p><p>Dissolve your<strong> vegetable stock mix</strong>, <strong>peanut butter</strong> and <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>creamed coconut</strong> in 350ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[500ml]<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span>[650ml] </span><strong>boiled water</strong> – this is your <strong>coconut stock</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1633344099044-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1633344099044-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1633344099044-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1633344099044-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1633344099044-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the onion has softened, add the <strong>chopped garlic</strong>, <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>ginger</strong>, <strong>ground turmeric</strong>, <strong>cayenne pepper </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!)<strong> </strong>and<strong> crushed coriander seeds</strong> to the pan and cook for 1-2 min or until fragrant</p><p>Increase the heat to medium, add your <strong>cherry tomatoes</strong> and <strong>coconut stock</strong> and cook for 7-9 min or until thickened</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1633344102098-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1633344102098-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1633344102098-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1633344102098-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1633344102098-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, chop most of your <strong>coriander</strong> finely, including the stalks (reserve some leaves for garnish!)</p><p>Add the<strong> roasted butternut squash</strong> and <strong>chopped coriander</strong> to the pan and cook for 1 min further – this is your <strong>Brazilian-style</strong> <strong>squash & coriander curry</strong></p><p>Add the juice of<strong> half</strong> your <strong>lime[s]</strong> to the curry</p><p>Cut the<strong> remaining lime</strong> into 1 wedge per person</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1633344107234-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1633344107234-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1633344107234-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1633344107234-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1633344107234-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>Brazilian-style squash & coriander curry</strong> over the <strong>cooked rice</strong></p><p>Garnish with the <strong>reserved coriander leaves</strong> and<strong> </strong>a<strong> lime wedge</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8,
      "media": {
        "images": []
      }
    }
